Microsoft is 4-0 (they took down Netscape, Suns Systems, MAC and IBM) and Google
may be their next target.<EOS> Google is probably making this move to counter
Microsoft Search using Encarta (it's online dictionary).<EOS> More below.<EOS> 

But it looks like Google isn't opening it's mouth about the reason behind the
offer as Linux News reports:<EOS> "While we don't have anything specific to announce
today, Google and the Wikimedia Foundation are collaboratively evaluating
creative ways to support Wikipedia.org and its community."<EOS> Sure Google, although
this would put it on coarse for global domination of the internet by 2014.<EOS> It
will be interesting to see whether or not Google will finally slay the Microsoft
Goliath, who has known no major defeat and seeks to vanquish all competition.<EOS>
Selah!<EOS> 

