Does a pacman absolutely need a uv lamp?<EOS> 

Or maybe something humid or heat?<EOS> 

I assume you are talking about a pacman frog.<EOS> No, technically they do not need a
UVB light; they are nocturnal.<EOS> However, it certainly wouldn't hurt if you wanted
to provide one.<EOS> A pacman frog will need a heat source that creates a basking
temp in the upper 80's F for at least 10 - 12 hours a day.<EOS> don't forget to use a
calcium supplement twice a week; captive reptiles are prone to calcium
deficiency.<EOS> 

